define InitialVolume 1 define CountPerLevel 30 define FlashAtTemperature 45 define StopAtTemperature 50
alias dTank d0 alias dPump d1 alias dConsoleVolume d2 alias dConsoleCount d3 alias dConsoleTemp d4 alias dFlashing d5
alias rTankTempInC r4 alias rPumpVolume r5 alias rPumpCount r6
Init: # Initialize the hardware to known state. s dPump On 0 s dFlashing On 0 s dConsoleVolume Setting 0 s dConsoleCount Setting 0
# Initialize pump volume/count variables. move rPumpVolume InitialVolume move rPumpCount 0
Main: # Update the volume/count displays. s dConsoleVolume Setting rPumpVolume s dConsoleCount Setting rPumpCount
# Update the temperature display from the small tank in celsius. l rTankTempInC dTank Temperature sub rTankTempInC rTankTempInC 273.15 s dConsoleTemp Setting rTankTempInC
# Check for the tank temperature is high enough to enable the flashing light. sge r0 rTankTempInC FlashAtTemperature s dFlashing On r0
# Check if the max temperature was reached and stop. bge rTankTempInC StopAtTemperature Stop
# Set the volume pump and make sure its running. s dPump Setting rPumpVolume s dPump On 1
# Yield for one second (i.e., one count == one second). yield yield
# Increment the volume count and loop if less than the CountPerLevel value. add rPumpCount rPumpCount 1 blt rPumpCount CountPerLevel Main
# Increment the pump volume. add rPumpVolume rPumpVolume 1
# Reset the count. move rPumpCount 0
# And repeat... j Main
Stop: # Make sure the pump is off to avoid badness. s dPump On 0
# Just loop forever as the test is over. yield j Stop
